he%20mines%20threaten%20wildlife%20and%20sacred%20sites.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20a%20lithium%20boom%20after%20years%20of%20laying%20the%20groundwork%20for%20an%20electric-vehicle%20supply%20chain%20that%20doesn't%20rely%20on%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20past%20month%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20approved%20the%20Rhyolite%20Ridge%20lithium-boron%20mine%20in%20Nevada%20and%20loaned%20%242.6%20billion%20to%20the%20company%20developing%20Thacker%20Pass%2C%20another%20lithium%20mine%20in%20the%20state.%20A%20project%20in%20California's%20Salton%20Sea%20started%20construction%20earlier%20this%20year.%20The%20three%20sites%2C%20expected%20to%20come%20online%20between%202026%20and%202028%2C%20would%20massively%20increase%20the%20US's%20lithium%20supply.%20Since%20the%201960s%2C%20only%20one%20site%2C%20Silver%20Peak%2C%20in%20Nevada%2C%20has%20operated%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20expansion%20is%20aimed%20at%20curbing%20China's%20control%20over%20the%20metals%20used%20in%20EV%20batteries%20and%20other%20renewable-energy%20technologies%20that%20countries%20need%20to%20decarbonize%20their%20economies.%20While%20most%20of%20the%20world's%20lithium%20is%20produced%20in%20Australia%20and%20South%20America%2C%20some%20two-thirds%20of%20it%20is%20processed%20in%20China%2C%20which%20also%20dominates%20EV-battery%20manufacturing.%20The%20US%20imports%20about%2025%25%20of%20its%20lithium%20supply%20from%20Chile%20and%20Argentina%2C%20but%20an%20analysis%20of%20federal%20data%20by%20the%20Atlantic%20Council%20found%20that%20it%20relied%20on%20China%20for%20about%2070%25%20of%20its%20lithium-ion%20batteries%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20electrifying%20the%20transportation%20industry%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20rely%20on%20any%20one%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Bernard%20Rowe%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20of%20Ioneer%2C%20which%20is%20developing%20Rhyolite%20Ridge%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20recognition%20that%20there%20had%20to%20be%20domestic%20production.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20customs%20officer%20holds%20powdery%20white%20lithium%20carbonate%20during%20an%20inspection%20at%20Shanghai%20%C4%B0nternational%20Port%20on%20June%206%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67229d579b3250dbbceb47d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20customs%20officer%20inspects%20imported%20lithium%20carbonate%20at%20Shanghai%20%C4%B0nternational%20Port%20on%20June%206%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EVCG%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20is%20encouraging%20US%20mining%20and%20manufacturing%20through%20a%20mix%20of%20loans%2C%20grants%2C%20tax%20breaks%2C%20and%20research%20and%20development%20programs%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lot%20of%20which%20was%20authorized%20under%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act.%20The%20incentives%20cover%20activities%20including%20extracting%20critical%20minerals%20like%20lithium%3B%20manufacturing%20solar%2C%20wind%2C%20and%20battery%20parts%3B%20buying%20EVs%3B%20and%20recycling%20components.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERowe%20argued%20that%20while%20the%20US%20alone%20can't%20meet%20the%20skyrocketing%20demand%20for%20lithium%20due%20to%20rising%20sales%20of%20EVs%20and%20battery%20storage%2C%20some%20of%20the%20supply%20has%20to%20be%20sourced%20domestically%20for%20national%20security%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKarl%20Friedhoff%2C%20a%20fellow%20for%20Asia%20studies%20at%20the%20Chicago%20Council%20on%20Global%20Affairs%2C%20agreed.%20He%20said%20there's%20no%20world%20in%20which%20the%20US%20and%20its%20partners%20can%20quickly%20compete%20with%20China%20on%20critical%20minerals%3B%20China%20already%20has%20so%20much%20capacity%20that%20it%20sets%20global%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20question%20then%20is%2C%20can%20the%20US%20and%20other%20partner%20countries%20create%20a%20supply%20chain%20that%20meets%20their%20basic%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20Friedhoff%2C%20who's%20part%20of%20a%20project%20exploring%20how%20the%20US%2C%20Japan%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20India%20can%20cooperate%20to%20shift%20supply%20chains%20away%20from%20China.%20%26quot%3BCan%20we%20supply%20our%20own%20batteries%3F%20Can%20we%20build%20our%20own%20battery%20technologies%3F%20Do%20we%20have%20enough%20rare-earth%20elements%20for%20defense%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20estimates%20from%20Ioneer%20and%20other%20lithium%20project%20developers%2C%20the%20US%20could%20produce%20more%20than%20enough%20supply%20for%20the%201.4%20million%20EVs%20sold%20in%20the%20country%20last%20year%2C%20which%20accounted%20for%207%25%20of%20the%20auto%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20wants%20EVs%20to%20account%20for%20at%20least%2050%25%20of%20car%20sales%20by%202030%2C%20and%20states%20like%20California%20and%20Texas%20are%20quickly%20deploying%20more%20battery%20storage%20to%20help%20balance%20stressed%20power%20grids.%20In%20September%2C%20the%20White%20House%20said%20US%20lithium%20production%20was%20on%20track%20to%20meet%20one-fifth%20of%20global%20demand%20outside%20of%20China%20this%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c11b28df-2899-481e-8b55-b52898315793%5C%22%3ESome%20environmentalists%2C%20Native%20tribes%20are%20alarmed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lithium%20projects%20haven't%20been%20without%20controversy%2C%20however.%20The%20Center%20for%20Biological%20Diversity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbiologicaldiversity.org%2Fw%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fblm-grants-final-approval-to-nevada-lithium-mine-threatening-biodiversity-cultural-landscapes-2024-10-24%2F%3F_gl%3D1*jmu4dt*_gcl_au*MTc3Mjg1OTA3Ni4xNzI5ODYzNzkz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20threatened%20to%20sue%20the%20Biden%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20its%20permit%20for%20Rhyolite%20Ridge%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20project%20could%20drive%20an%20endangered%20wildflower%20to%20extinction.%20The%20Western%20Shoshone%20Defense%20Project%2C%20which%20works%20to%20protect%20the%20Western%20Shoshone%20peoples'%20native%20homelands%2C%20says%20the%20mine%20threatens%20local%20water%20sources%20and%20culturally%20important%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Tiehm's%20buckwheat%20plant%20in%20Esmeralda%20County%2C%20Nevada%2C%20grows%20beside%20where%20the%20Rhyolite%20Ridge%20lithium-boron%20mine%20is%20planned.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67229c2c01ea6d83dee53c29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Tiehm's%20buckwheat%20plant%20in%20Esmeralda%20County%2C%20Nevada%2C%20grows%20beside%20where%20the%20Rhyolite%20Ridge%20lithium-boron%20mine%20is%20planned.%3Cp%3ERobyn%20Beck%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThacker%20Pass%20faced%20similar%20opposition%2C%20but%20a%20federal%20judge%20last%20year%20dismissed%20a%20lawsuit%20from%20three%20Native%20tribes%20who%20argued%20that%20the%20mine's%20construction%20near%20a%20sacred%20site%20along%20Nevada's%20border%20with%20Oregon%20violated%20the%20law%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Flithium-mine-tribes-climate-energy-lawsuit-nevada-7a65eee7d78d93a1e44e3f8e10445143%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20AP%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERowe%20said%20Ioneer%20redesigned%20the%20Rhyolite%20Ridge%20mine%20to%20limit%20its%20footprint%20in%20the%20critical%20habitat%20of%20the%20endangered%20wildflower%2C%20Tiehm's%20buckwheat.%20He%20said%20Ioneer%20would%20also%20monitor%20the%20pollinator%20population%20and%20adopt%20dust-control%20strategies.%20The%20Biden%20administration%2C%20in%20issuing%20the%20permit%20for%20the%20mine%2C%20said%20it%20would%20not%20jeopardize%20the%20flower's%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%