20a%20modern%20miracle%20%E2%80%94%20not%20merely%20because%20of%20all%20the%20tech%20packed%20into%20your%20iPhone%2C%20but%20for%20the%20simple%20reason%20that%20all%20those%20houses%20are%20gathered%20in%20one%20place.%20Open%20up%20Zillow%2C%20Redfin%2C%20or%20any%20of%20their%20competitors%2C%20and%20you'll%20have%20a%20clear%20picture%20of%20almost%20all%20the%20homes%20up%20for%20grabs%20around%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20may%20be%20about%20to%20change.%20Real%20estate's%20power%20players%20are%20engaged%20in%20a%20bitter%20standoff%20over%20who%20exactly%20gets%20to%20see%20the%20millions%20of%20homes%20listed%20for%20sale%20in%20the%20US%20each%20year.%20At%20the%20center%20of%20the%20debate%20are%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-lawsuits-buy-sell-homes-forever-housing-market-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple-listing%20services%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20MLSes%2C%20local%20databases%20that%20gather%20pictures%20and%20details%20of%20homes%20for%20sale.%20Almost%20as%20soon%20as%20a%20real-estate%20agent%20starts%20touting%20a%20home%20publicly%20%E2%80%94%20via%20an%20email%20blast%2C%20a%20post%20on%20their%20website%2C%20or%20a%20sign%20in%20a%20front%20yard%20%E2%80%94%20they'll%20throw%20the%20listing%20on%20the%20MLS%20to%20be%20fed%20to%20other%20agents%20and%20aggregator%20sites%20like%20Zillow.%20Smart%20business%20move%3F%20Sure.%20But%20agents%20also%20don't%20have%20a%20choice%2C%20thanks%20to%20a%20rule%20handed%20down%20five%20years%20ago%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawsuits-verdict-realtors-brokerages-real-estate-agents-home-buying-selling-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epowerful%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bclear-cooperation%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20requires%20them%20to%20list%20a%20home%20on%20the%20MLS%20within%20one%20business%20day%20of%20marketing%20it%20to%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20industry's%20high-profile%20figures%20are%20pushing%20for%20the%20NAR%20to%20loosen%20the%20rule%20or%20get%20rid%20of%20it%2C%20which%20they%20say%20would%20give%20sellers%20and%20their%20agents%20more%20freedom%20to%20choose%20where%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20whom%20%E2%80%94%20they%20advertise%20their%20properties.%20The%20NAR's%20top%20brass%20are%20set%20to%20consider%20the%20change%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cynical%20take%20is%20that%20those%20in%20favor%20of%20a%20shake-up%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20leaders%20of%20some%20of%20the%20country's%20largest%20real-estate%20brokerages%2C%20like%20Compass%20and%20Anywhere%20Real%20Estate%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20big-name%20brands%20like%20Coldwell%20Banker%20and%20Century%2021%20%E2%80%94%20just%20want%20to%20hoard%20listings%20on%20their%20own%20websites.%20As%20gatekeepers%2C%20the%20thinking%20goes%2C%20they'll%20be%20able%20to%20lure%20agents%20and%20clients%20with%20exclusive%20access%20to%20these%20properties%2C%20growing%20their%20businesses%20and%20padding%20their%20bottom%20lines.%20The%20result%20would%20be%20a%20more%20fractured%20market%3B%20instead%20of%20going%20to%20just%20Zillow%20or%20Realtor.com%2C%20a%20buyer%20might%20have%20to%20comb%20through%20individual%20brokerages'%20websites.%20Agents%20might%20be%20emboldened%20to%20share%20listings%20among%20private%20networks%20of%20in-the-know%20brokers%20rather%20than%20market%20them%20to%20everyone.%20More%20homes%20could%20trade%20hands%20out%20of%20view%20of%20the%20average%20homebuyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20to%20ask%20people%2C%20'Should%20houses%20be%20hidden%3F'%20most%20people%20would%20say%20no%2C%26quot%3B%20Brian%20Boero%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%201000Watt%2C%20a%20brand%20and%20marketing%20agency%20for%20real-estate%20companies%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20asked%20people%2C%20'Should%20everybody%20be%20able%20to%20see%20the%20houses%20that%20are%20for%20sale%20on%20the%20market%20at%20any%20time%20and%20have%2C%20at%20least%2C%20access%20to%20them%3F'%20I%20think%20most%20people%20would%20say%20absolutely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20quite%20so%20cut-and-dried.%20Opponents%20of%20the%20rule%20say%20sellers%20should%20be%20able%20to%20market%20their%20homes%20however%20they%20see%20fit%2C%20arguing%20that%20there%20are%20all%20kinds%20of%20reasons%20someone%20might%20not%20want%20to%20list%20their%20home%20on%20the%20MLS.%20And%20if%20the%20goal%20is%20a%20transparent%20market%20that%20prioritizes%20consumers%2C%20the%20clear-cooperation%20policy%20is%20a%20flawed%20tool.%20It%20contains%20a%20glaring%20loophole%20that%20critics%20say%20may%20have%20actually%20pushed%20%3Cem%3Emore%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehome%20sales%20into%20the%20shadows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20latest%20conflict%20pits%20Goliath%20against%20Goliath%2C%20but%20the%20stakes%20are%20highest%20for%20the%20millions%20of%20Davids%20just%20trying%20to%20put%20roofs%20over%20their%20heads.%20The%20typical%20buyer%20wants%20to%20see%20all%20the%20homes%20available%2C%20while%20the%20typical%20seller%20wants%20a%20quick%20sale%20and%20a%20good%20price.%20Which%20kind%20of%20housing%20market%20will%20get%20them%20there%3F%20Both%20sides%20claim%20to%20know%20the%20answer%2C%20but%20their%20visions%20for%20the%20future%20of%20homebuying%20are%20miles%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20not-so-distant%20past%2C%20MLSes%20distributed%20home%20listings%20via%20books%20%E2%80%94%20thick%2C%20unwieldy%20tomes%20that%20were%20outdated%20by%20the%20time%20they%20made%20it%20into%20a%20real-estate%20agent's%20hands.%20The%20introduction%20of%20the%20online%20MLS%20around%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century%20was%20a%20revelation%2C%20providing%20a%20central%20repository%20of%20reliable%20info%20on%20an%20area's%20available%20homes.%20The%20system%20isn't%20perfect%3A%20Access%20to%20the%20MLS%20is%20often%20restricted%20to%20licensed%20agents%20who%20pay%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20in%20dues%20each%20year%20to%20belong%20to%20their%20local%2C%20state%2C%20and%20national%20Realtor%20associations%2C%20on%20top%20of%20MLS%20fees.%20Since%20there%20are%20more%20than%20500%20local%20MLSes%20in%20the%20US%2C%20an%20agent%20might%20have%20to%20pay%20dues%20to%20several%20of%20these%20groups%20just%20to%20see%20all%20the%20homes%20within%20an%20hour's%20drive%20of%20their%20office.%20But%20the%20databases%20are%20still%20widely%20considered%20a%20model%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20an%20agent%20doesn't%20technically%20have%20to%20participate%2C%20the%20MLS's%20trove%20of%20data%20is%20practically%20a%20necessity%20to%20do%20the%20job.%20And%20in%20order%20to%20play%20in%20the%20MLS%20sandbox%2C%20you%20have%20to%20follow%20the%20MLS%20rules.%20About%2097%25%20of%20local%20MLSes%20are%20effectively%20controlled%20by%20the%20NAR%2C%20a%20trade%20group%20with%20roughly%201.5%20million%20members%20who%20pay%20for%20the%20%26quot%3BRealtor%26quot%3B%20designation%20and%20agree%20to%20abide%20by%20the%20organization's%20ethical%20and%20professional%20guidelines.%20The%20NAR%20doesn't%20own%20the%20MLSes%20directly%2C%20but%20it%20sets%20the%20rules%20for%20most%20of%20them.%20Five%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20organization's%20leaders%20pinpointed%20a%20growing%20problem%3A%20Some%20agents%20weren't%20playing%20fair.%20They%20were%20keeping%20select%20listings%20off%20the%20MLS%20and%20marketing%20them%20on%20their%20own%20websites%20or%20among%20clubby%20groups%20of%20brokers%20known%20as%20private%20listing%20networks.%20The%20prevalence%20of%20so-called%20pocket%20listings%20has%20always%20been%20hard%20to%20quantify%2C%20but%20pretty%20much%20everyone%20agrees%20they%20were%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20years%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20Redfin%20estimated%20that%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202019%2C%20about%201.7%25%20of%20listings%2C%20or%20some%2018%2C000%20homes%2C%20were%20likely%20pocketed.%20Those%20homes%20were%20marked%20%26quot%3Bsold%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bpending%20sale%26quot%3B%20the%20same%20day%20they%20were%20put%20in%20the%20MLS%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sign%20that%20the%20transaction%20may%20have%20already%20been%20wrapped%20up%20in%20private.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgents%20promoting%20pocket%20listings%20might%20argue%20that%20they%20were%20acting%20in%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20their%20clients%3B%20a%20seller%20going%20through%20a%20messy%20divorce%2C%20for%20example%2C%20may%20prefer%20a%20quiet%20sales%20process%20rather%20than%20the%20fanfare%20of%20a%20public%20listing.%20The%20MLS%20also%20displays%20information%20that%20may%20not%20be%20favorable%20to%20a%20seller.%20It%20shows%20the%20number%20of%20days%20a%20home%20has%20been%20on%20the%20market%20and%20keeps%20track%20of%20price%20cuts%2C%20offering%20buyers%20leverage%20points%20that%20would%20never%20be%20found%20on%20a%20listing%20broker's%20website.%20There%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20self-serving%20reasons%20an%20agent%20might%20prefer%20to%20advertise%20a%20home%20off%20the%20MLS.%20If%20they%20find%20an%20unrepresented%20buyer%2C%20they%20may%20be%20able%20to%20pocket%20the%20portion%20of%20the%20commission%20that%20would%20have%20otherwise%20gone%20to%20the%20buyer's%20agent%2C%20upping%20their%20haul%20from%20the%20sale%20to%2C%20say%2C%206%25%20instead%20of%20the%20typical%203%25.%20Belonging%20to%20private%20listing%20networks%20could%20also%20help%20drum%20up%20business%3A%20%3Cem%3EWork%20with%20me%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20an%20agent%20could%20tell%20a%20buyer%2C%20%3Cem%3Eand%20you'll%20get%20access%20to%20all%20these%20listings%20that%20Joe%20Schmo%20at%20XYZ%20Brokerage%20doesn't%20even%20know%20about.%20%3C%2Fem%3EIndeed%2C%20Top%20Agent%20Network%2C%20a%20destination%20for%20high-achieving%20brokers%20to%20share%20%26quot%3Bnot-yet-on-MLS%20properties%26quot%3B%20with%20each%20other%2C%20claims%20on%20its%20website%20that%20agents%20can%20help%20buyers%20find%20their%20dream%20homes%20%26quot%3Bby%20staying%20ahead%20of%20the%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20point%20of%20the%20MLS%2C%20though%2C%20is%20to%20have%20all%20listings%20in%20one%20place%20for%20everyone%20to%20find%20%E2%80%94%20the%20system%20falls%20apart%20if%20agents%20get%20to%20pick%20and%20choose%20which%20ones%20to%20contribute.%20The%20NAR's%20answer%20to%20this%20chaos%20was%20the%20clear-cooperation%20policy.%20The%20rule%2C%20which%20went%20into%20effect%20in%20May%202020%2C%20tightened%20the%20screws%20on%20agents%20by%20requiring%20them%20to%20put%20a%20listing%20on%20the%20MLS%20within%20one%20business%20day%20of%20marketing%20it%20to%20the%20public.%20For-sale%20sign%20in%20the%20front%20yard%3F%20Better%20get%20it%20on%20the%20MLS%20pronto.%20Gush%20about%20it%20on%20your%20Facebook%20page%3F%20Clock's%20ticking.%20Teasing%20homes%20in%20a%20private%20listing%20network%20without%20also%20posting%20on%20the%20MLS%20was%20a%20no-go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20was%20that%20any%20alternative%20to%20the%20MLS%20would%20harm%20both%20consumers%20and%20their%20agents.%20A%20seller%20risks%20getting%20a%20lower%20price%20if%20there%20are%20fewer%20eyeballs%20on%20their%20listing.%20A%20buyer%20might%20know%20of%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20homes%20for%20sale%20at%20any%20time%2C%20limiting%20their%20options.%20Agents%20can't%20make%20money%20off%20shadow%20listings%20that%20they%20don't%20even%20know%20about.%20MLSes%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbad-real-estate-agents-realtors-homebuyers-sellers-housing-market-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuge%20sources%20of%20revenue%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20many%20local%20Realtor%20associations%20that%20own%20and%20operate%20them%20%E2%80%94%20the%20NAR%20has%20a%20direct%20interest%20in%20making%20sure%20they%20remain%20valuable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20benefits%20when%20we%20all%20pool%20our%20listings%2C%20and%20we%20do%20so%20in%20a%20timely%20manner%2C%26quot%3B%20Saul%20Klein%2C%20a%20longtime%20real-estate%20executive%20who's%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20San%20Diego%20Multiple%20Listing%20Service%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20people%20are%20hurt%2C%20potentially%2C%20when%20we%20don't%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20rule%2C%20however%2C%20included%20a%20loophole.%20It%20allows%20agents%20to%20market%20a%20home%20to%20other%20agents%20%3Cem%3Ewithin%20%3C%2Fem%3Etheir%20brokerage%20without%20sharing%20it%20on%20the%20MLS%2C%20a%20practice%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Boffice%20exclusives.%26quot%3B%20The%20carveout%20effectively%20allows%20for%20private%20gardens%20within%20each%20brokerage%2C%20filled%20with%20homes%20you%20can't%20find%20anywhere%20else.%20Large%20brokerages%20like%20Compass%2C%20which%20has%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20agents%20across%20the%20country%2C%20can%20make%20a%20pitch%20to%20a%20seller%20like%20this%3A%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20maintain%20your%20privacy%20by%20keeping%20your%20home%20off%20Zillow%20and%20test%20your%20chosen%20price%20across%20our%20huge%20network.%20We%20can%20limit%20the%20showings%20so%20you%20don't%20have%20random%20people%20traipsing%20through%20your%20home.%20And%20if%20you're%20not%20satisfied%2C%20we%20can%20always%20turn%20to%20the%20MLS%20later.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20many%20large%20brokerages%20tout%20offerings%20that%20attempt%20to%20capitalize%20on%20this%20state%20of%20play.%20Compass%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20will%20offer%20to%20list%20your%20home%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bprivate%20exclusive%26quot%3B%20within%20its%20brokerage%20before%20launching%20it%20to%20the%20public.%20Howard%20Hanna's%20%26quot%3BFind%20It%20First%26quot%3B%20program%20allows%20sellers%20to%20%26quot%3Bbenefit%20from%20broad%20exposure%20without%20compromising%20on%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company's%20CEO%2C%20Howard%20Hanna%20IV%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20In%20a%20lawsuit%20after%20the%20unveiling%20of%20the%20rule%2C%20Top%20Agent%20Network%20accused%20the%20NAR%20of%20privileging%20large%20brokerages%20(which%20belong%20to%20the%20association)%20while%20stamping%20out%20the%20competition%20from%20alternatives%20to%20the%20MLS.%20It%20complained%20that%20the%20organization's%20rule%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20transparent%20attempt%20at%20protecting%20its%20turf%2C%20not%20helping%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20clear-cooperation%20rule%20faded%20into%20the%20background%20as%20the%20pandemic%20upended%20the%20industry.%20But%20as%20the%20market%20settled%20and%20other%20big%20changes%2C%20like%20the%20class-action%20lawsuits%20over%20agent%20commissions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuyers-real-estate-revolution-nar-lawsuits-new-rules-realtors-agents-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereached%20a%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20group%20led%20by%20Compass'%20CEO%2C%20Robert%20Reffkin%2C%20began%20publicly%20pressuring%20the%20NAR%20to%20reconsider%20clear%20cooperation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-housewives-mauricio-umansky-agency-daily-schedule-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMauricio%20Umansky%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20celebrity%20agent%20and%20brokerage%20CEO%20known%20for%20appearing%20on%20%26quot%3BBuying%20Beverly%20Hills%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BReal%20Housewives%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BDancing%20with%20the%20Stars%2C%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20already%20part%20of%20the%20opposition%20to%20the%20rule%2C%20having%20sued%20the%20NAR%20over%20his%20attempts%20to%20start%20an%20MLS%20alternative%20known%20as%20the%20PLS%2C%20or%20the%20Property%20Listing%20Service.%20Executives%20at%20Anywhere%20Real%20Estate%2C%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20brokerage%20companies%20in%20the%20country%2C%20have%20pushed%20for%20the%20rule%20to%20be%20loosened%20but%20not%20eliminated%20%E2%80%94%20one%20suggestion%20is%20to%20give%20agents%20more%20time%20to%20market%20a%20home%20publicly%20before%20listing%20it%20on%20the%20MLS.%20On%20the%20other%20side%2C%20executives%20at%20Zillow%20and%20Redfin%20decried%20the%20potentially%20disastrous%20consequences%20of%20a%20fractured%20housing%20market.%20In%20a%20recent%20op-ed%20article%2C%20Redfin's%20president%20and%20CEO%2C%20Glenn%20Kelman%2C%20argued%20that%20the%20end%20of%20clear%20cooperation%20would%20allow%20large%20brokerages%20to%20control%20more%20inventory%2C%20forcing%20buyers%2C%20sellers%2C%20and%20their%20agents%20to%20flock%20to%20big%20players%20rather%20than%20smaller%20outfits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20in%20weakening%20Clear%20Cooperation%20is%20to%20make%20being%20bigger%20matter%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20being%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelman%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20the%20law%20of%20the%20jungle%2C%20masquerading%20as%20freedom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%2C%20though%2C%20that%20the%20clear-cooperation%20rule%20made%20things%20much%20better%20for%20consumers.%20In%20a%20hot%20market%2C%20it's%20easier%20for%20brokers%20to%20market%20a%20home%20off%20the%20databases%20and%20still%20get%20it%20sold.%20Redfin%20estimates%20that%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202021%2C%20the%20share%20of%20listings%20that%20were%20likely%20pocketed%20increased%20to%202.8%25%2C%20or%20almost%2035%2C000%20homes.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-higher-home-prices-fewer-sales-inventory-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20market%20has%20since%20slowed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Redfin's%20estimation%20of%20pocket%20listings%20was%20down%20to%201.8%25%20of%20sales%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%20this%20year%2C%20roughly%20in%20line%20with%20the%20same%20period%20in%202019.%20These%20are%20imperfect%20estimates%3B%20it's%20possible%20for%20a%20home%20to%20debut%20on%20the%20MLS%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20have%20a%20sale%20pending%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%20without%20anything%20unscrupulous%20happening.%20They%20could%20also%20be%20undercounts%2C%20since%20some%20homes%20may%20never%20be%20listed%20in%20the%20MLS%20at%20all.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20data%20from%20one%20of%20clear%20cooperation's%20biggest%20advocates%20doesn't%20prove%20that%20the%20rule%20has%20actually%20reduced%20off-MLS%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20%3Cem%3Ehas%20%3C%2Fem%3Echanged%20since%20the%20rule%20went%20into%20effect%20is%20brokerages'%20eagerness%20to%20control%20access%20to%20home%20listings.%20Home%20sales%20volume%20has%20plummeted%20since%20the%20heady%20days%20of%202021%2C%20which%20means%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompass-layoffs-robert-reffkin-housing-market-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20revenue%20for%20the%20businesses%20that%20make%20their%20money%20by%20taking%20a%20cut%20of%20their%20agents'%20sales%20commissions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Without%20clear%20cooperation%2C%20brokerages%20could%20drive%20more%20traffic%20to%20their%20own%20websites%20by%20publicly%20advertising%20homes%20that%20aren't%20available%20in%20the%20MLS%20or%20on%20sites%20like%20Zillow.%20And%20they%20could%20continue%20to%20tease%20office%20exclusives%20that%20are%20accessible%20only%20if%20you%20work%20with%20their%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20sides%20of%20this%20debate%20can%20reasonably%20claim%20that%20the%20industry%20will%20face%20legal%20trouble%20if%20they%20don't%20get%20their%20way.%20The%20Department%20of%20Justice%2C%20which%20has%20been%20fighting%20to%20reopen%20a%20wide-ranging%20investigation%20into%20the%20NAR%2C%20has%20signaled%20that%20the%20organization's%20control%20of%20the%20MLSes%20could%20be%20anticompetitive%2C%20stifling%20the%20development%20of%20alternative%20databases.%20What%20incentive%20is%20there%20for%20someone%20to%20start%20an%20MLS%20rival%2C%20the%20thinking%20goes%2C%20if%20basically%20everyone%20who%20uses%20the%20new%20database%20would%20still%20have%20to%20put%20their%20listings%20on%20the%20MLS%20anyway%3F%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20proponents%20of%20clear%20cooperation%20argue%20that%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20showing%20homes%20to%20everybody%20could%20run%20afoul%20of%20fair-housing%20laws%20designed%20to%20ensure%20that%20buyers%20have%20equal%20access%20to%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20every%20listing%20is%20contributed%20to%20the%20MLS%20and%20that%20every%20consumer%20has%20access%20to%20that%20information%20is%20an%20enormous%20and%20overwhelming%20benefit%20to%20support%20fair%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20Victor%20Lund%2C%20a%20founder%20and%20managing%20partner%20of%20Wav%20Group%2C%20a%20consulting%20firm%20for%20real-estate%20companies%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20too%20much%20opportunity%20for%20housing%20discrimination%20without%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20ways%20this%20could%20go.%20The%20final%20call%20will%20rest%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20top%20leaders%20at%20NAR%2C%20whose%20board%20will%20likely%20mull%20over%20the%20issue%20at%20its%20annual%20convention%20in%20the%20second%20week%20of%20November.%20It%20could%20be%20months%20before%20a%20decision%2C%20however%2C%20especially%20since%20it's%20not%20clear%20what%20kinds%20of%20actions%20the%20DOJ%20may%20take%20against%20the%20organization.%20NAR%20leadership%20could%20keep%20clear%20cooperation%20as%20is%2C%20repeal%20it%20entirely%2C%20or%20revise%20it%20in%20ways%20that%20might%20not%20even%20be%20obvious%20right%20now.%20Several%20people%20I%20spoke%20with%2C%20including%20Kelman%2C%20told%20me%20they'd%20like%20to%20see%20the%20office-exclusive%20loophole%20closed%20%E2%80%94%20no%20more%20exceptions%20for%20agents%20marketing%20homes%20within%20their%20brokerages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20haven't%20bought%20a%20home%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelman%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20nothing%20more%20unsettling%20than%20seeing%20a%20moving%20van%20outside%20a%20house%20that%20never%20showed%20up%20in%20any%20of%20your%20searches.%26quot%3B%20An%20imperfect%20rule%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20is%20better%20than%20no%20rule.%20Those%20in%20Kelman's%20camp%20say%20a%20housing%20market%20without%20the%20current%20version%20of%20the%20MLS%20would%20be%20more%20divided%20and%20more%20difficult%20to%20parse.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it's%20impossible%20to%20brush%20aside%20the%20criticisms%20of%20the%20rule.%20There's%20no%20guarantee%20it%20will%20remain%20as%20it%20is%20when%20the%20dust%20settles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuits%20over%20agent%20commissions%20last%20year%20were%20seismic%2C%20but%20they%20were%20ultimately%20about%20the%20practical%20matter%20of%20consumers'%20wallets%3A%20how%20much%20they%20were%20paying%20agents%20and%20what%20they%20were%20getting%20in%20return.%20The%20debate%20over%20clear%20cooperation%20strikes%20me%20as%20much%20more%20existential.%20Its%20result%20will%20determine%20the%20kind%20of%20housing%20market%20we%20have%20in%20the%20future.%20Buckle%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-fight-clear-cooperation-realtors-zillow-pocket-listings-homes-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730368021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6720fb3801ea6d83dee4b7ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-fight-clear-cooperation-realtors-zillow-pocket-listings-homes-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Real%20estate's%20power%20players%20are%20engaged%20in%