-expat-vote-for-trump-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Esupportive%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20he%20too%20withholds%20his%20views%20of%20the%20conflict%20around%20his%20coworkers.%20He%20worries%20that%20one%20colleague%2C%20who%20is%20outspoken%20in%20her%20opposition%20to%20Israel's%20treatment%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20would%20have%20more%20questions%20than%20he's%20willing%20or%20prepared%20to%20answer.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20say%20anything%20about%20it%2C%20because%20my%20thoughts%20are%20sometimes%20very%20opposite%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Fernando%2C%20who%20asked%20for%20partial%20anonymity%20to%20protect%20his%20relationships.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWithholding%20one's%20real%20views%2C%20or%20what%20public-opinion%20researchers%20call%20%26quot%3Bself-silencing%2C%26quot%3B%20appears%20to%20be%20widespread%20in%20the%20US.%20As%20part%20of%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpopulace.org%2Fresearch%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Enew%20study%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20think%20tank%20Populace%20and%20the%20research%20firm%20YouGov%20conducted%20a%20survey%20in%20the%20US%20in%20which%2058%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20thought%20most%20people%20don't%20feel%20comfortable%20expressing%20their%20honest%20opinions%20about%20sensitive%20issues%20and%2061%25%20said%20that%20in%20the%20past%20year%20they%20themselves%20had%20%26quot%3Bavoided%20saying%20things%20that%20they%20believe%20because%20others%20might%20find%20them%20offensive.%26quot%3B%20The%20study%2C%20%26quot%3BSocial%20Pressure%20Index%3A%20Private%20Opinion%20in%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20of%20more%20than%2019%2C000%20respondents%20found%20evidence%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20all%20demographic%20groups%20%E2%80%94%20age%2C%20gender%2C%20race%2C%20income%2C%20and%20political%20party%20%E2%80%94%20had%20self-silenced%20in%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BSocial%20norms%20have%20made%20it%20costly%20to%20express%20views%20that%20one%20considers%20to%20be%20controversial%2C%20and%20therefore%20people%20withhold%20those%20views%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20James%20Gibson%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20government%20at%20Washington%20University%20in%20St.%20Louis%20who's%20studied%20public%20opinion%20for%20more%20than%2040%20years%20and%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20Populace's%20study.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20everyone%20agrees%20that%20all%20private%20views%2C%20regardless%20of%20how%20objectionable%20they%20are%2C%20should%20be%20voiced%20in%20the%20public%20square%20or%20even%20at%20home.%20The%20old%20saying%20%26quot%3Bno%20politics%20at%20the%20dinner%20table%26quot%3B%20seems%20to%20have%20existed%20since%20there%20have%20been%20politics%20to%20talk%20about%20at%20dinner%20tables.%20Pushing%20certain%20views%20that%20violate%20basic%20social%20norms%20out%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiscourse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Ediscourse%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20can%20be%20a%20powerful%20form%20of%20accountability%20and%20a%20way%20to%20shape%20public%20debate%20for%20the%20better.%20But%20critics%20of%20self-censorship%20argue%20that%20when%20too%20many%20people%20aren't%20saying%20what%20they%20actually%20think%2C%20it%20inhibits%20the%20vigorous%20public%20debate%20necessary%20for%20a%20healthy%20society.%20%26quot%3BIf%20people%20are%20self-censoring%2C%20deliberation%20is%20compromised%20and%20that's%20very%2C%20very%20damaging%2C%20in%20my%20view%2C%20to%20democracy%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20says.%20The%20study%20found%20that%20the%20more%20people%20self-silence%2C%20the%20less%20they%20trust%20other%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20final%20sprint%20of%20another%20bilious%20and%20barbed%20US%20presidential%20election%20season%2C%20where%20the%20final%20polls%20show%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20and%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20a%20deadlock%2C%20it's%20clear%20the%20country%20is%20deeply%20divided.%20Public-opinion%20experts%20say%20polarization%20perpetuates%20self-censorship%20by%20creating%20an%20environment%20where%20the%20perceived%20costs%20of%20dissent%20are%20higher.%20%26quot%3BYour%20brain%20assumes%20the%20loudest%20voices%20repeated%20the%20most%20are%20the%20majority%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Todd%20Rose%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Populace%20and%20a%20former%20professor%20at%20Harvard's%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Education.%20People%20fear%20repercussions%20for%20expressing%20opinions%20that%20differ%20from%20what%20they%20perceive%20to%20be%20the%20majority%20viewpoint.%20In%20turn%2C%20dishonest%20public%20debate%20makes%20us%20believe%20that%20we're%20more%20divided%20than%20we%20really%20are.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BSelf-silencing%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20just%20saying%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20Rose%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20can%20end%20up%20leading%20to%20this%20place%20where%20public%20consensus%20looks%20very%20different%20than%20private%20consensus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20more%20we%20know%20about%20what%20we%20actually%20believe%2C%20the%20likelier%20we%20may%20be%20to%20meet%20in%20the%20middle.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerica%20seems%20to%20be%20suffering%20from%20what%20the%20German%20political%20scientist%20Elisabeth%20Noelle-Neumann%20coined%20in%20the%201970s%20as%20a%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F228049403_The_Spiral_of_Silence_A_Theory_of_Public_Opinion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Espiral%20of%20silence%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%26quot%3B%20Noelle-Neumann%20argued%20that%20people%20are%20reluctant%20to%20share%20their%20opinions%20on%20controversial%20topics%20when%20they%20subconsciously%20perceive%20that%20the%20majority%20disagrees%20with%20them.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20majority%20views%20come%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20dominant%20over%20time%2C%20shrinking%20room%20for%20conversation%20and%20compromise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20reality%2C%20we%20very%20well%20might%20agree%20on%20a%20lot%20more%20than%20we%20admit%20to%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20try%20to%20measure%20people's%20private%20views%2C%20the%20Populace%20researchers%20used%20what's%20called%20the%20list-experiment%20method.%20This%20involved%20dividing%20respondents%20into%20two%20groups.%20One%20was%20presented%20a%20series%20of%20lists%20each%20containing%20three%20statements%20(e.g.%2C%20%26quot%3BClass%20size%20significantly%20affects%20student%20achievement%26quot%3B).%20The%20other%20was%20presented%20with%20a%20series%20of%20identical%20lists%20but%20with%20a%20fourth%20statement%20added%20%E2%80%94%20these%20extra%20statements%20were%20the%20ones%20that%20the%20researchers%20were%20actually%20interested%20in%20testing%20(e.g.%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20support%20school%20choice%20in%20public%20education%26quot%3B).%20For%20each%20list%2C%20respondents%20were%20asked%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Ehow%20many%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20the%20statements%20they%20agreed%20with%2C%20an%20indirect%20line%20of%20questioning%20meant%20to%20encourage%20honest%20responses.%20The%20researchers%20could%20then%20compare%20the%20two%20groups'%20answers%20to%20estimate%20how%20many%20people%20actually%20agreed%20with%20the%20statements%20being%20tested.%20Finally%2C%20the%20researchers%20conducted%20a%20separate%2C%20%26quot%3Bpublic%26quot%3B%20survey%20in%20which%20a%20different%20set%20of%20people%20were%20asked%20directly%20whether%20they%20agreed%20or%20disagreed%20with%20the%20statements%20being%20tested.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETake%20abortion%2C%20as%20one%20example.%20Populace%20found%20that%20Protestant%2C%20Roman%20Catholic%2C%20Jewish%2C%20and%20Muslim%20respondents%20in%20the%20list%20experiment%20were%20all%20more%20likely%20than%20comparable%20respondents%20in%20the%20public%20survey%20to%20support%20the%20idea%20that%20%26quot%3Babortion%20should%20be%20legal%20in%20most%20cases.%26quot%3B%20While%20just%2039%25%20of%20Protestants%20in%20the%20traditional%20survey%20agreed%20with%20that%20statement%2C%20Populace%20estimated%20that%2054%25%20agreed%20in%20the%20private%20structure.%20Among%20Muslims%2C%20the%20difference%20was%2043%25%20agreeing%20with%20the%20statement%20versus%20an%20estimated%2066%25%20who%20privately%20agreed.%20Overall%2C%20Populace%20found%20that%2055%25%20of%20respondents%20publicly%20said%20abortion%20should%20be%20legal%20in%20most%20cases%2C%20compared%20with%2063%25%20thought%20to%20have%20privately%20agreed.%20(Both%20figures%20were%20far%20higher%20than%20those%20in%20polling%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F20%2F2024%2F05%2FPP_2024.5.13_abortion_TOPLINE.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EPew%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F321143%2Famericans-stand-abortion.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EGallup%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20included%20question%20wording%20with%20a%20wider%20range%20of%20possible%20responses%20than%20the%20agree-disagree%20format%20of%20the%20Populace%20study.)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDemocrats%20and%20Republicans%20were%20also%20more%20privately%20aligned%20on%20the%20question%20of%20defunding%20the%20police.%20While%2027%25%20of%20Democratic%20respondents%20publicly%20agreed%20with%20the%20statement%20%26quot%3BI%20support%20defunding%20the%20police%2C%26quot%3B%20just%203%25%20privately%20supported%20the%20movement.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20just%201%25%20of%20Republicans%20privately%20supported%20it%20and%206%25%20publicly%20supported%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20survey%20also%20found%20that%20Republicans%20and%20wealthier%20people%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20privately%20feel%20that%20society%20isn't%20fair%20than%20they%20publicly%20acknowledged.%20Rose%20posited%20that%20Democrats%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20publicly%20concerned%20with%20unfairness%2C%20particularly%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20marginalized%20groups.%20Republicans%20define%20themselves%20in%20opposition%20to%20that.%20That%20dynamic%20is%20on%20display%20in%20this%20election%20as%2C%20for%20example%2C%20former%20Trump%20attacks%20Harris%20for%20defending%20a%20federal%20law%20that%20permits%20government-funded%20gender-affirming%20healthcare%20for%20prisoners%20and%20migrants.%20But%20privately%2C%20they%20acknowledged%20that%20they%20agree.%20While%2050%25%20of%20Republicans%20publicly%20said%20%26quot%3Bwe%20live%20in%20a%20mostly%20fair%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20just%2011%25%20privately%20agreed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20thing%20liberals%20and%20conservatives%20might%20secretly%20agree%20on%3A%20that%20they%20don't%20trust%20the%20government%2C%20at%20all.%20Democrats%20were%20far%20more%20likely%20to%20differ%20in%20their%20private%20and%20public%20responses%20on%20this%3A%20While%2036%25%20publicly%20agreed%20with%20the%20statement%20%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20I%20trust%20the%20government%20to%20tell%20me%20the%20truth%2C%26quot%3B%20just%205%25%20were%20estimated%20to%20have%20privately%20agreed.%20Similarly%2C%202%25%20of%20Republicans%20were%20thought%20to%20privately%20trust%20the%20government%20to%20tell%20the%20truth%2C%20while%2014%25%20said%20so%20publicly.%20Other%20surveys%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fpolitics%2F2015%2F11%2F23%2F1-trust-in-government-1958-2015%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Esimilarly%20found%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20historically%20low%20levels%20of%20trust%20in%20major%20institutions%20like%20the%20government%20and%20the%20media%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERose%20is%20particularly%20concerned%20about%20low%20levels%20of%20trust%20%E2%80%94%20of%20the%20government%2C%20the%20media%2C%20and%20other%20people.%20A%20lack%20of%20social%20trust%20causes%20people%20to%20resent%20each%20other%2C%20look%20for%20scapegoats%2C%20and%20become%20susceptible%20to%20demagoguery%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBy%20almost%20any%20measure%2C%20social%20trust%20is%20a%20phenomenal%20predictor%20of%20the%20health%20and%20vibrancy%20of%20democracies%2C%26quot%3B%20Rose%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20everyone%20is%20convinced%20that%20American%20society%20is%20suffering%20from%20a%20complete%20breakdown%20in%20societal%20trust.%20Gibson%20argues%20the%20long-established%20survey%20measure%20of%20whether%20we%20trust%20each%20other%20%E2%80%94%20agreement%20with%20the%20statement%20that%20%26quot%3Bin%20general%2C%20most%20people%20can%20be%20trusted%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20is%20too%20vague%20to%20be%20accurate.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20build%20in%20some%20context%20to%20let%20people%20know%20what%20the%20question%20is.%20You%20can't%20allow%20their%20imagination%20just%20to%20go%20crazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOverall%2C%20certain%20groups%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20political%20independents%2C%20and%20college%20graduates%20%E2%80%94%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20produce%20dramatically%20different%20results%20in%20the%20public%20and%20private%20surveys%2C%20Populace%20found.%20Gibson%20speculated%20that%20this%20might%20be%20because%20these%20groups%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20aware%20of%20social%20norms%2C%20and%20sensitive%20to%20the%20costs%20of%20violating%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGen%20Zers%2C%2072%25%20of%20whom%20said%20they%20had%20self-silenced%20in%20the%20past%20year%2C%20might%20be%20influenced%20by%20their%20heavy%20use%20of%20social%20media%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Bmakes%20it%20very%20easy%20to%20manufacture%20false%20consensus%2C%26quot%3B%20Rose%20argues.%20They%20also%20have%20a%20particularly%20keen%20awareness%20of%20being%20harassed%20or%20canceled%20for%20voicing%20unpopular%20opinions.%20For%20wealthier%20and%20more-educated%20people%2C%20the%20costs%20of%20offending%20customers%2C%20an%20audience%2C%20a%20fellow%20country-club%20member%2C%20or%20a%20business%20partner%20might%20be%20higher.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20society%20where%20reputation%20matters%20a%20lot%2C%20in%20an%20attention%20economy%2C%20there's%20actually%20a%20lot%20more%20incentive%20to%20hold%20views%20that%20are%20consistent%20with%20what%20you%20think%20people%20want%20to%20hear%2C%26quot%3B%20Rose%20says.%20The%20risks%20of%20social%20ostracism%20might%20not%20be%20as%20acute%20for%20lower-income%20people%20and%20those%20with%20less%20education%2C%20as%20they're%20often%20already%20socially%20and%20economically%20excluded.%20And%20ironically%2C%20the%20Silent%20Generation%20(born%20from%201928%20to%201945)%20reported%20self-silencing%20the%20least.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEngaging%20in%20public%20debate%20or%20even%20just%20a%20dinner-table%20discussion%20can%20be%20contentious%20and%20uncomfortable.%20But%20Rose%20and%20Gibson%20argue%20that%20the%20only%20way%20to%20build%20a%20less%20polarized%20and%20self-censoring%20society%20is%20through%20hard%20conversations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20start%20to%20find%20the%20moral%20courage%20to%20be%20honest%20with%20each%20other%2C%20respectfully%2C%26quot%3B%20Rose%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20you're%20going%20to%20see%20the%20revealing%20of%20a%20common%20ground%20that%20we%20can%20start%20to%20anchor%20in%20and%20start%20to%20try%20to%20solve%20some%20of%20the%20real%20problems%20we%20face%20as%20a%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20revelation%2C%20however%2C%20will%20have%20to%20wait%20until%20after%20Election%20Day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feliza-relman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EEliza%20Relman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20policy%20correspondent%20focused%20on%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20on%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdemocrats-republicans-harris-trump-voters-secret-opinions-polarization-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730366701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67212dc7a0a0cc14f224b010%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdemocrats-republicans-harris-trump-voters-secret-opinions-polarization-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump%20and%20Harris%20voters%20are%20lying%20to%20their%20friends%20about%20what%20they%20really%20believe.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdemocrats-republicans-harris-trump-voters-secret-opinions-polarization-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%223rd%20Test%3A%20Bring%20KL%20Rahul%20in%20or%20not%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730366444000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114813229%2Cimgsize-100540.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnew-zealand-in-india%2Fwill-india-retain-the-playing-xi-or-give-kl-rahul-a-chance-in-the-final-new-zealand-test%2Farticleshow%2F114813021.cms%22%2C%2