0number%20of%20movers%20to%20and%20from%20each%20state%20between%202022%20and%202023.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENew%20York%20lost%20residents%20at%20the%20highest%20rate%2C%20followed%20by%20New%20Jersey%20and%20Illinois.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPeople%20are%20often%20driven%20to%20move%20for%20lower%20costs%20of%20living%2C%20a%20professor%20who%20studies%20migration%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJackie%20Nguyen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-cost-of-living-nyc-kansas-city-midwest-rent-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleft%20New%20York%20for%20Kansas%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Missouri%2C%20in%202020.%20After%20a%20year%20there%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20stay%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20she%20hadn't%20previously%20considered%20moving%20away%20from%20a%20big%20coastal%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20I%20feel%20like%20I'm%20a%20big%20fish%20in%20a%20small%20pond.%20I've%20never%20experienced%20that%20before.%20It's%20cheaper%20here%2C%20and%20I%20have%20a%20better%20quality%20of%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Nguyen%20told%20Business%20Insider's%20Dan%20Latu%20in%20January%2C%20when%20she%20was%2035.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20I%20want%20millennials%20to%20know.%20There%20are%20huge%20opportunities%20in%20these%20smaller%20secondary%20cities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECensus%20data%20released%20on%20October%2017%20indicates%20that%20New%20York%20recorded%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20people%20moving%20out%20of%20all%2050%20states.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20481%2C000%20people%20left%20New%20York%20for%20another%20state%20between%202022%20and%202023%2C%20while%20just%20over%20302%2C800%20moved%20into%20the%20Empire%20State%20from%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FDOVrg%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Net%20moving%20rates%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22531%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fdata%2Ftables%2Ftime-series%2Fdemo%2Fgeographic-mobility%2Fstate-to-state-migration.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20data%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20comes%20from%20the%20American%20Community%20Survey%2C%20which%20includes%20responses%20to%20questions%20concerning%20moving%20patterns.%20Business%20Insider%20calculated%20each%20state's%20net%20moving%20rate%20by%20comparing%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20moved%20into%20and%20out%20of%20each%20state%20per%201%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c6375cdc-90cc-4b2c-89ad-1020d1c46d1d%5C%22%3EThe%20states%20people%20move%20out%20of%20the%20most%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20all%2050%20states%2C%20New%20York%20ranks%20last%20with%20a%20net%20moving%20rate%20of%20-9.23.%20(Washington%20DC%2C%20however%2C%20had%20a%20lower%20rate%20of%20-11.16.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next-most-left%20state%20was%20New%20Jersey%2C%20followed%20by%20Illinois%2C%20Alaska%2C%20and%20Louisiana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-people-leaving-california-moved-to-these-states-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalifornia%20lost%20more%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20New%20York%20did%3A%20690%2C100.%20But%20because%20of%20its%20larger%20population%20and%20the%20greater%20number%20of%20movers%20into%20the%20Golden%20State%2C%20California's%20net%20migration%20rate%20lands%20right%20after%20Louisiana's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20census%20data%20illuminates%20how%20people%20tend%20to%20move%20from%20more%20expensive%20to%20more%20affordable%20areas%2C%20according%20to%20Sarah%20Dickerson%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20and%20research%20economist%20at%20the%20Kenan%20Institute%20of%20Private%20Enterprise%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%20couple%20years%2C%20we've%20seen%20people%20leaving%20these%20big%20expensive%20cities%2C%20places%20like%20New%20York%20City%2C%20Los%20Angeles%20%E2%80%94%20that%20typically%20we%20think%20of%20as%20magnets%20for%20talent%20migration%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dickerson%2C%20who%20studies%20moving%20and%20housing.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20continued%20to%20see%20this%20trend%2C%20in%20part%2C%20because%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20cost%20of%20housing%20is%20especially%20high%20in%20the%20Northeast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2218589e15-03f3-4502-a129-faeb541b6595%5C%22%3EMany%20movers%20are%20drawn%20to%20southern%20states%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20less-crowded%20states%20are%20drawing%20a%20relatively%20large%20number%20of%20movers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorth%20Dakota%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20about%20780%2C000%20residents%20to%20New%20York's%2020%20million%20%E2%80%94%20had%20the%20highest%20net%20migration%20rate%20at%2017.55.%20Between%202022%20and%202023%2C%2034%2C415%20people%20moved%20into%20North%20Dakota%2C%20while%2020%2C814%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuality%20assurance%20analyst%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-living-in-bismarck-north-dakota-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDavrick%20Hayes%20told%20BI%20in%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20high%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20long%20commute%20times%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20prompted%20him%20to%20move%20to%20Bismarck%2C%20North%20Dakota.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20obscenely%20cheap%20to%20live%20here%20and%20doesn't%20require%20a%20roommate%20just%20to%20afford%20a%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Hayes%2C%20then%2031%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20apartment%20I%20first%20moved%20into%20was%20%24800%20a%20month%3B%20the%20same%20apartment%20in%20LA%20would%20have%20been%20at%20least%20%242%2C500.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20drawing%20movers%20at%20the%20second-highest%20rate%20was%20South%20Carolina.%20North%20Carolina%20was%20fourth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20seen%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20moving%20to%20the%20Carolinas%20in%20general%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dickerson%2C%20who%20is%20based%20in%20Raleigh%2C%20North%20Carolina.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20fact%20there%20are%20job%20opportunities%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%20than%20many%20other%20areas%20on%20the%20East%20Coast.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-north-carolina-pros-and-cons-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENorth%20Carolina's%20midsize%20cities%20are%20luring%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20bigger%20cities%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-south-carolina-retirement-taxes-weather-cost-of-living-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESouth%20Carolina%20is%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-south-carolina-retirement-taxes-weather-cost-of-living-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epopular%20with%20retirees%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20beach%20at%20dusk%20with%20the%20tide%20lapping%20up%20on%20the%20sand%20as%20a%20few%20people%20walk%20through%20ankle-deep%20waters%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f307b4d17aa3c7b2b59cec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHilton%20Head%20Island%20in%20South%20Carolina.%3Cp%3EEverett%20Atlas%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVermont%20(with%20about%20650%2C000%20people)%20and%20Delaware%20(with%20about%201%20million)%20lured%20a%20large%20number%20of%20new%20residents%20relative%20to%20their%20populations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20states%20probably%20benefited%20from%20denizens%20of%20nearby%20cities%20%E2%80%94%20like%20Boston%2C%20for%20Vermont%2C%20and%20Washington%20DC%2C%20for%20Delaware%20%E2%80%94%20being%20drawn%20to%20their%20relatively%20cheaper%20homes%20and%20slower%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20see%20happening%20on%20the%20East%20Coast%20is%20likely%20part%20of%20that%20broader%20theme%20of%20cost%20of%20living%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BCost%20of%20housing%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20driving%20some%20of%20the%20trends%20that%20we're%20continuing%20to%20see%20in%20migration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-states-people-are-leaving-for-cheaper-life-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730365982000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67228ddc9b3250dbbceb3f16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-states-people-are-leaving-for-cheaper-life-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Americans%20leave%20New%20York%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20and%20Illinois%20at%20the%20highest%20rates%2C%20according%20to%20newly%20released%20census%20data.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy%2CNoah%20Sheidlower%2CDan%20Latu)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-states-people-are-leaving-for-cheaper-life-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Avantika%20stuns%20in%20a%20saree%20on%20Diwali%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730365935000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114812221%2Cimgsize-37800.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Favantika-embraces-her-culture-and-sends-out-diwali-greetings-to-fans-admits-i-often-struggle-with-%2Farticleshow%2F114812140.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left